At Itosugi, we offer sushi and kappo style cuisine. Kappo translates to “cut” and to “cook.” This cuisine has its origins in western Japan, and employs a wide range of cooking techniques. The result is a multi-course menu with each dish showcasing a specific technique, prepared at the counter in front of the customer. Our aim is to make sushi and kappo style dishes using the best seasonal ingredients which North America has to offer, with a focus on the ingredients of the Pacific Northwest.

Our culinary passion is inspired by our terroir. 

“Itosugi” is the Japanese word for cypress — one of the most iconic trees in Canada.

Give us a call! It'll be the best choice you've ever made!

We're offering satisfying, top of the line burgers with a Japanese twist. Customers are attracted to us for our creative products and exceptional customer service. We make it a priority to ensure that our clients are more than satisfied.

attributes.about_this_biz_history:
In 2002, founder Allan Christian found himself working with and living on Glen Valley Organic Farm Co-Op in the Fraser Valley helping them raise money to keep the farm operational.  He grew up on a traditional farm in Saskatchewan and even though he had left that behind years ago, he found himself getting involved in a more hands-on way; fixing machinery, mending fences, weeding and helping with the harvesting. He absolutely loved it and claimed those years on the farm were some of his happiest.

Allan was always adventurous in the kitchen and during a visit from his mother they baked pies together with the apples that had fallen from the trees in the orchard. He was also an adventurous entrepaneur who had started many successful businesses in his career. He thought that an organic pie shop in the city would be a big hit, and with lots of determination, hard work and sweat equity, he opened the pie shop in April 2003.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties:
Aphrodite's is more than a restaurant and pie shop, it's a community fiercely dedicated to wild, organic, local and sustainable food. We work directly with local farms and producers to ensure that our menu has the smallest ecological footprint possible. We're a home for the sustainable food movement in Vancouver, supporting local farmers, producers, artists, charities and non-profits. For us, it's bigger than pie - it's food you can feel good 
about.

Aphrodite's Pie Shop is where it all began back in 2003; a cute and cozy retail bakery and coffee shop, spreading the love of local, organic ingredients one slice at a time.
Today it still has the same warm feel;  it's a place where you can slow down for a moment, step back in time in the old heritage building and enjoy a mug of homemade chai with a slice of pie (or a fresh muffin), while you catch up with friends or a good book that you picked up from our neighbours, Banyen Books!

Our fruit and cream pies are made from all organic ingredients including local organic fruits and berries. We also have organic wheat and gluten free pies and vegan pies for those with special dietary requirements.

attributes.about_this_biz_history:
Best friends Thuy Kelp & Rose Concepcion have shared a passion for creating fresh and delicious food for over a decade.

Since the late eighties, they have gained valuable experience while working in acclaimed kitchens across North America, in 2003, they brought their combine creative passion to Vancouver's West Point Grey Village and opened MIX The Bakery.

This neighbourhood, artisan bakery & cafe have become a comforting meeting place for locals, while providing signature products for the finest restaurants in town.  Thuy and Rose, along with their culinary team, are dedicated to providing Vancouver with unique and tasty delectables, in a wamr and welcome atmosphere!
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties:
We specialize in our award-winning artisan breads and baked goods.  We have proudly operated our comforting neighbourhood cafe as well as supplied our artisan bread to the city's finest kitchens.

At MIX The Bakery, we use time-honoured techniques, which are balanced with unique flavours and textures.  Our line of hand made breads include varieties from around the world and is individually designed to our high qaulity standards.  No short cuts are taken in our processes, as we believe this yields the freshest and tastiest results.

In addition, we offer creative catering to satisfy any breakfast, lunch, or party get-together.  We have a variety of sandwiches, salads, and sweets in our menu but we welcome any suggestions to create off-menu items for special occasions.

MIX The Bakery also has a line of all-natural artsinal preserves made in house. They are recognized by Vancouver Magazine as one of the Top 101 Things to Taste in BC and can be found in local markets and specialty stores.
Here at The Kitchen we specialize in all types of Korean food, we are a Local Korean Restaurant serving lunch and dinner!

attributes.about_this_biz_history:
The Galley is located in the Jericho Sailing Centre Association building. The building was originally the machine shop for a World War II-era air force base. By the 1960s, the building was abandoned and in serious disrepair. Some students from UBC convinced the Parks Board to buy the building and turn it into a public ocean access centre for human and wind powered craft (sailboats, kayaks, windsurfing, stand-up paddle boards). 

In 1990, we opened a small restaurant on the second floor. Over the last 25 years, we have expanded into a popular, 130-seat patio restaurant, with an unmatched 180 degree view of English Bay.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties:
With a beautiful and unique view of English Bay, the Galley Patio offers some of the best summer dining in Vancouver. We have great burgers, fantastic grilled sockeye salmon, and excellent salads. We make the best fish & chips in town, and we have legendary nachos.

We are casual, fun, and family-friendly. Located on the second floor of the large grey building on the beach between Jericho and Spanish Banks, we are open to the public.

attributes.about_this_biz_history:
Gather is the residence dining room inside Place Vanier, a first year student residence on the University of British Columbia Vancouver campus. 

Place Vanier is named after Georges Vanier, a distinguished war figure in both World Wars and the first French-Canadian Governor General. Place Vanier first opened in 1959 with the commons block and two houses. By 1968 there were twelve houses. 

Gather serves daily meals to the nearly 1500 students who live in Place Vanier, UBC staff and faculty, and the campus community. In summer, Place Vanier and Gather open as a hostel and accommodation for conference guests.
attributes.about_this_biz_specialties:
Globally inspired, locally sourced meals are our passion! Gather serves up fresh, healthy, West Coast contemporary cuisine with global inspiration seven days a week. Where else can you find gourmet burgers, Vij's Indian, Latin American street food, sushi burritos, and a salad bar serving UBC Farm produce all in one place?

Fresh seafood is Ocean Wise™ certified, we serve local and/or organic fruits and vegetables, and our beef burgers and fresh chicken are halal.

attributes.about_this_biz_history: In 1958, two brothers borrowed $600 from their mom to open a pizza place in Wichita, Kansas. They named it Pizza Hut because their sign only had room for eight letters. How profound! Soon, the restaurant grew. Why? The pizza was awesome. The service felt like home. And the customers were treated like family. And we've been delivering that same food and service ever since. For the Love of Pizza Since 1958. From day one, the Carney brothers could look their customers in the eye and promise them the finest pizza in town -- because they knew the farmers who grew the ingredients, and they knew those farmers cared about quality. Since then, our farmers have grown right alongside us, and the ingredients we use are still our highest priority. No one loves pizza more than Pizza Hut. That's why pizza is in our name -- and always will be.
